body:
With the current version (go1.6, linux/amd64), godoc renders note markers consisting of multiple paragraphs incorrectly.

An example can be found here:
https://golang.org/pkg/sync/atomic/#pkg-note-BUG

The actual note marker is
```go
// BUG(rsc): On x86-32, the 64-bit functions use instructions unavailable before the Pentium MMX.
//
// On non-Linux ARM, the 64-bit functions use instructions unavailable before the ARMv6k core.
//
// On both ARM and x86-32, it is the caller's responsibility to arrange for 64-bit
// alignment of 64-bit words accessed atomically. The first word in a global
// variable or in an allocated struct or slice can be relied upon to be
// 64-bit aligned.
```

godoc currently renders this note as a single paragraph:
```html
<a href="/src/sync/atomic/doc.go?s=1207:1656#L36">â˜ž</a>
On x86-32, the 64-bit functions use instructions unavailable before the Pentium MMX.

On non-Linux ARM, the 64-bit functions use instructions unavailable before the ARMv6k core.

On both ARM and x86-32, it is the caller's responsibility to arrange for 64-bit
alignment of 64-bit words accessed atomically. The first word in a global
variable or in an allocated struct or slice can be relied upon to be
64-bit aligned.
```
but it should probably render it using multiple paragraphs.
